    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Lebetus patzneri (Teleostei: Gobiidae), a new goby species from the Balearic Islands, western Mediterranean, with first records of Lebetus guilleti (Le Danois, 1913) from this area and Norway, and with notes on its biology" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567348>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567344>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567346>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567350>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567352>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567342>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567340>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567354>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567338> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567348>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., head lateral line system of the holotype ZSM 47486, female, 16.6 mm SL, from off SW Mallorca Island, 72 m depth. Terminology in text. Drawing by M. Kovačić." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567348/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567344>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., SEM aspects of the paratype ZSM 46865, female, 16.8 mm SL; from off SW Mallorca Island, 60m depth. a: right lateral view; b: ventral view of pelvic fins and urogenital papilla. SEM photo by A. Cerwenka." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567344/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567346>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., MicroCT reconstruction of the paratype ZSM 46865, female, 16.8 mm SL; from off SW Mallorca Island, 60m depth. a: left lateral view; b: dorsal view; c: ventral view. MicroCT reconstruction by A. Cerwenka." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567346/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567350>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., right saccular otolith of the paratype ZSM 46865, female, 16.8 mm SL; from off SW Mallorca, 60m depth. a: in medial/inner view; b: left otolith in anterior view. Orientation of otolith with respect to fish symmetry is indicated as follows: a, anterior; d, dorsal; l, lateral; m, medial; p, posterior; v, ventral. MicroCT reconstruction by A. Cerwenka." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567350/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567352>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., aspects of the paratype and two unpreserved specimens in life coloration shortly after collection. a: left lateral view of paratype ZSM 46865, female, 16.8 mm SL; from off SW Mallorca Island, 60m depth (based on montage of two separate photographs (slight artifacts at montage suture at about D1 origin due to slightly different position of the specimen between the two photographs); b: left dorsolateral view of head and anterior flank view of paratype ZSM 46865; c: left lateral view of the second known specimen (unpreserved), unknown size, Menorca channel, 67m depth (based on montage of two separate photographs; stitching artifacts visible before D1 origin); d: left slightly dorsolateral view of third known specimen (unpreserved) of unknown size, Menorca channel, 67m depth. Photographs by F. Ordines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567352/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567342>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., aspects of the preserved holotype, reversibly stained with Cyanine Blue, ZSM 47486, female, 16.6 mm SL, from off SW Mallorca Island, 72 m depth, preserved. a: left lateral view b: dorsal view; c: ventral view. Photographs by M. Kovačić." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567342/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567340>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Lebetus patzneri sp. nov., aspects of the freshly collected holotype, ZSM 47486, female, 16.6 mm SL, from off SW Mallorca Island, 72 m depth, preserved. a: left lateral view; b: right lateral view; c: ventral view; c: dorsal view; d: ventral view left lateral view. Photographs by F. Ordinas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567340/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567354>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Maximum likelihood phylogenetic tree topology depicting the phylogenetic position and small intraspecific genetic distance of COI-barcode haplotypes (520 bp) of the holotype of Lebetus patzneri sp. nov. and five Lebetus guilleti from the northeastern Atlantic (Norway, two specimens), the Western Mediterranean (Baleares, one specimen) and from the northern Adriatic (Croatia, two specimens). All sand goby genera are included, except for Hyrcanogobius and Pseudaphya. Numbers on branches are bootstrap support values (%) for the Maximum Likelihood analysis (values below 50% not shown). Tip labels are composed of the genus and species name followed by ZSM collection number (if newly sequenced in this study) or of the GenBank accession number. Inserted photos depict the second known specimen of L. patzneri sp. nov. (as Fig. 8c; upper photograph) and the first L. guilleti specimen photographed and collected in 15m depth in Norway (ZSM-PIS-GO 1227; lower photograph). Photographs above and below by F. Ordines and R. Svensen, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567354/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567338>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map showing the three sampling stations where all the individuals of Lebetus patzneri sp. nov. (stars) and L. guilleti newly recorded individuals (circles) from the Balearic Islands were collected. The holotype and the paratype of L. patzneri sp. nov. were collected from the sampling station in the Menorca Channel and off southeast Mallorca, respectively. The holotype, paratype and the two unpreserved specimens off south Menorca were collected at 72, 60 and 67 m, respectively. The 50, 100, 500 and 800 m isobaths are shown. Map drawn by F. Ordinas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3567338/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

